<?xml version="1.0"?><h:html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2002/xforms" xmlns:ev="http://www.w3.org/2001/xml-events" xmlns:h="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xmlns:jr="http://openrosa.org/javarosa" xmlns:odk="http://www.opendatakit.org/xforms" xmlns:orx="http://openrosa.org/xforms" xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema"><h:head><h:title>OSCE_Caring for a hemovac drain</h:title><model odk:xforms-version="1.0.0"><instance><data id="osce1_form" version="1.1"><intro><reserved_name_for_field_list_labels_3/><step1/><step2/><step3/><step4/><step5/><step6/><step7/><step8/><step9/><step10/><step11/><step12/><step13/><step14/><step15/><step16/><step17/></intro><meta><instanceID/></meta></data></instance><bind nodeset="/data/intro/reserved_name_for_field_list_labels_3" type="string"/><bind nodeset="/data/intro/step1" required="true()" type="string"/><bind nodeset="/data/intro/step2" required="true()" type="string"/><bind nodeset="/data/intro/step3" required="true()" type="string"/><bind nodeset="/data/intro/step4" required="true()" type="string"/><bind nodeset="/data/intro/step5" required="true()" type="string"/><bind nodeset="/data/intro/step6" required="true()" type="string"/><bind nodeset="/data/intro/step7" required="true()" type="string"/><bind nodeset="/data/intro/step8" required="true()" type="string"/><bind nodeset="/data/intro/step9" required="true()" type="string"/><bind nodeset="/data/intro/step10" required="true()" type="string"/><bind nodeset="/data/intro/step11" required="true()" type="string"/><bind nodeset="/data/intro/step12" required="true()" type="string"/><bind nodeset="/data/intro/step13" required="true()" type="string"/><bind nodeset="/data/intro/step14" required="true()" type="string"/><bind nodeset="/data/intro/step15" required="true()" type="string"/><bind nodeset="/data/intro/step16" required="true()" type="string"/><bind nodeset="/data/intro/step17" required="true()" type="string"/><bind jr:preload="uid" nodeset="/data/meta/instanceID" readonly="true()" type="string"/></model></h:head><h:body class="pages"><group appearance="field-list" ref="/data/intro"><select1 appearance="label" ref="/data/intro/reserved_name_for_field_list_labels_3"><label> </label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step1"><label>Goal: The drain is patent and intact.Review the physician's order for drain and site care or the nursing plan of care related to drain care.</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step2"><label>Gather the necessary supplies.</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step3"><label>Identify the patient.</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step4"><label>Explain the procedure to the patient.</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step5"><label>Assess the patient for possible need for nonpharmacologic pain-reducing interventions or analgesic medication prior to wound care dressing change. Administer appropriate analgesic, consulting physician's orders, and allow enough time for analgesic to achieve its effectiveness.</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step6"><label>Perform hand hygiene. .</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step7"><label>Close the room door or curtains. Place the bed at an appropriate and comfortable working height.</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step8"><label>Assist the patient to a comfortable position that provides easy access to the drain area. Use the bath blanket to cover any exposed area other than the drain. Place the waterproof pad under the drain site.</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step9"><label>Put on clean gloves and other personal protective equipment, such as mask or face shield, as necessary.</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step10"><label>Place the graduated collection container under the pouring spout of the drain. Without contaminating the outlet valve, uncap the valve. The chamber will expand completely as it draws in air. Empty the chamber's contents completely into the container. Use the alcohol pad to clean the chamber's spout and cap. Fully compress the chamber by pushing the top and bottom together with your hands. Keep the device tightly compressed while you reinsert the plug.</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step11"><label>Check the patency of the equipment. Make sure the tubing is free from twists and kinks.</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step12"><label>Secure the Hemovac drain to the patient's gown below the wound with pins, making sure that there is no tension on the tubing.</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step13"><label>Carefully measure and record the character, color, and amount of the drainage. Discard the drainage according to facility policy</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step14"><label>If the drain site has a dressing, redress the site. Assess the patient for possible need for pain/analgesic medication prior to dressing change.</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step15"><label>If the drain site is open to air, observe the sutures that secure the drain to the skin. Look for signs of pulling, tearing, swelling, or infection of the surrounding skin.</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step16"><label>Gently clean the sutures with the gauze pad soaked in normal saline. Dry with a new gauze pad.</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step17"><label>Remove gloves and all remaining equipment, place the patient in a position of comfort with side rails up and bed in the lowest position, and perform hand hygiene</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1></group></h:body></h:html>